    public interface Navigable<T>
extends DomainTypeDescriptor<T>
    Models a "piece" of the application's domain model that can be navigated as part of a query or the NavigableVisitationStrategy contract.

      • finishInitialization

        default boolean finishInitialization(Object bootReference,
                                     RuntimeModelCreationContext creationContext)
        Finish initialization step. It's important to understand that the runtime creation process will call this method on the navigable until one of several conditions are met
        • All navigables have returned true.
        • The navigable returned false and needs to wait for other dependencies.
        • The list of navigables have some missing or cyclic dependency
        Parameters:
        bootReference -
        creationContext - The context in which the Navigable is being created and finalized.
        Returns:
        true if initialization complete, false if not yet done.
